00:20:05.000 --> 00:20:12.000
And so I can do that by going like this.

00:20:12.000 --> 00:20:17.000
And this is a kind of important Python kind of got you,

00:20:17.000 --> 00:20:23.000
which is that I want to make sure whenever I'm using an external data set that I want to change,

00:20:23.000 --> 00:20:26.000
that I'm not modifying it in place.

00:20:26.000 --> 00:20:31.000
So what I usually like to do is just call a copy method on that data.

00:20:31.000 --> 00:20:37.000
So that basically ensures that whatever happens down here is going to be not going to modify this,

00:20:37.000 --> 00:20:40.000
like, original data frame in place.

00:20:40.000 --> 00:20:45.000
