And so if you're working on, say, you're working with team members who are using Python,

00:23:13.000 --> 00:23:17.000
and you want to have something where everybody can work on the same application,

00:23:17.000 --> 00:23:22.000
and they might not know R or be interested in learning R, that's one benefit.

00:23:22.000 --> 00:23:27.000
If you're wrapping, if your application is mostly a wrapper around some Python code,

00:23:27.000 --> 00:23:30.000
like you're using a large language model or something like that,

00:23:30.000 --> 00:23:35.000
it'll usually be a little bit easier to manage those dependencies in a pure Python application

00:23:35.000 --> 00:23:39.000
