The idea behind this library is that we're giving you the sort of bricks that we think you need to be able to build a wide variety of applications.

00:38:19.000 --> 00:38:27.000
And then for the most part, once you kind of get into it, since Shiny doesn't really care what's in this function.

00:38:27.000 --> 00:38:29.000
You can sort of do whatever you want to with it.

00:38:29.000 --> 00:38:33.000
So long as you have some Python code that can generate the output that you're looking for.

00:38:33.000 --> 00:38:35.000
For the most part, it'll work.

00:38:35.000 --> 00:38:37.000
There's some where it's a new library.

