I might instead of having this code in Shiny, I might have some other place where I'm just defining the plotting functions like and then just calling, you know, I might have a function that just was not a reactive function that was just took some data and generated this plot.

00:53:57.000 --> 00:54:04.000
So then maybe I have like maybe I have a function called draw histogram.

00:54:04.000 --> 00:54:10.000
And then that's just calling like just taking a data frame.

00:54:10.000 --> 00:54:19.000
And the advantage of this is that it really simplifies like of course anytime you're running something in a reactive context.

00:54:19.000 --> 00:54:20.000
It's more complicated.

